{
  "texts": [
    "In this way, DH-SNNs do not obviously increase storage and computational costs compared to vanilla SNNs.",
    "As given in Fig. 6a, the increase of parameters of DH-SNNs over vanilla SNNs is neuron-wise and proportional to the number of dendritic branches, which can be neglected compared to the heavy synaptic weights.",
    "Furthermore, we quantitatively present the numbers of parameters and synaptic operations of vanilla SNNs and DH-SNNs with different numbers of dendritic branches.",
    "We collect results from one-layer SFNNs and SRNNs on the SSC dataset and show the results in Fig. 6b.",
    "As predicted, there is no obvious increase of parameters and synaptic operations as the number of dendritic branches grows."
  ]
}